  "standtag": "As of Jun 22, 6:20 AM AWST · Two new Jun 21 finals locked: Spain 4-0 Saudi Arabia (Group H) and Belgium 0-0 Iran (Group G), both confirmed by 2+ sources (ESPN, Sky, FIFA, Opta) · GROUPS G & H recomputed (Spain to 4 pts and top of H; Iran & Belgium level on 2 in G); Cape Verde's opening-draw point corrected · SCORERS: Oyarzabal added on 2 (Messi & David still lead on 3) · Uruguay-Cape Verde and New Zealand-Egypt had not kicked off / not final at refresh time, so left pending · NEWS rotated to five fresh, multi-source verified surrounding-the-cup stories",
  "refreshedLine": "Refreshed Jun 22, 2026 (6:20 AM AWST). Added two newly confirmed Jun 21 results: Spain 4-0 Saudi Arabia (Yamal, Oyarzabal x2, Al Tambakti og) and Belgium 0-0 Iran (Ngoy red card), each verified by at least two independent sources. Group H now has Spain on 4 points and top; Group G has Iran and Belgium level on 2. Cape Verde's point from the 0-0 draw with Spain was also corrected. Oyarzabal joins the 2-goal group in SCORERS, with Messi and David still leading the Golden Boot race on 3. The later Jun 21 games (Uruguay-Cape Verde, New Zealand-Egypt) had not finished at refresh time and were left unchanged. NEWS rotated to five fresh, multi-source stories: Iran's enforced same-night U.S. exits and FIFA complaint (ESPN/Al Jazeera/CBS); Cape Verde keeper Vozinha's breakout (ESPN/Yahoo/Al Jazeera); the hydration-break backlash (Yahoo/ESPN/Al Jazeera); Tunisia sacking Lamouchi mid-tournament for Renard (ESPN/Fox); and climate scientists' heat warnings across host venues (Climate Central/Scientific American/Al Jazeera)."
